iva)-chickpea (Cicer arietinum) crop sequence (1999) IRRN, 24 (3), p. 25; Six, J., Ogle, S.M., Breidt, F.J., Conant, R.T., Mosier, A.R., Paustian, K., The potential to mitigate global warming with no-tillage management is only realized when practised in the long term (2004) Global Change Biology, 10, pp. 155-160; Watson, R.T., Zinyowera, M.C., Moss, R.H., Dokken, D.J., Climate change (1995), impacts, adaptations and mitigation of climate change. Scientific Technical Report Analyses (1996) Contribution of Working Group II to the Second Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, p. 880. , Watson, R.T., Zinyowera, M.C., Ross, R.H. (Eds.), Cambridge, New York; Yadav, R.L., Dwivedi, B.S., Pandey, P.S., Rice-wheat cropping system: Assessment of sustainability under green manuring and chemical fertilizer inputs (2000) Field Crops Research, 65, pp. 15-30; Ying, Z., Boecky, P., Chen, G.X., Van Cleemput, O., Influence of Azolla on methane emission from rice fields (2000) Nutrient Cycling in Agroecosystem, 58, pp. 321-326; Yu, K., Patrick Jr., W.H., Redox window with minimum global warming potential contribution from rice soils (2004) Soil Science Society America Journal, 68, pp. 2086-2091","Pathak, H.; Institut fur Meteorology und Klimaforschung, Kreuzeckbahnstr. 19, 82467 Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany; email: hpathak_cass@yahoo.com",,,,,,,,13522310,,AENVE,,"English","Atmos. Environ.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-27544467057
